,Recommended,233230,30033753,Posted: 19 February,all,The Laissez Pharaoh,"Imagine a walking simulator, except with all the interesting aspects of walking simulators (narrative, interesting environmental storytelling, etc.) removed, and replaced with some puzzles and nothing else. That's Kairo.It's not a bad game; if all you're looking for is a slow paced, bare-bones puzzle game then you'll enjoy it. The puzzles can be a little on the punishing side, but in general they're reasonably well executed and somewhat engaging.In short, if you want a first-person puzzle game which includes puzzles, a first-person perspective, and absolutely nothinng else, then Kairo is for you.A good game is any game that hits the target it's aiming at, even if it's not necessarily the most interesting target in the world. Kairo is far from the most engaging game ever made, but it achieves what it set out to do competently, so it gets a recommendation."
