76561198082489809,Recommended,233230,11715254,"Posted: 15 August, 2014",all,amarao,"Astonishingly aesthetic. I can't say 'beautiful', but aesthetic it is. Grotesque and gigantic scale, rough surfaces and brilliant presentation of empty space. This is pure art - you getting concrete feeling of empty space (pun intended), visualization of nothingness and monolithness.Sound environment and indirect interactions make it bewitching and slightly frightening, like you suddenly got eye-to-eye with something which is too big to grasp.Puzzles are not 'puzzles' in terms of 'solving', but in terms of 'finding the puzzle'. Understand the rules of interaction, find patterns in that interaction, and only after that solve it. Solving is not main part, recognition is.The best game without human narrative I ever saw."
