76561198292631324,Not Recommended,233230,28209012,"Posted: 5 December, 2016",all,76561198292631324,"Kairohas managed to annoy me, that is why the negative vote. Apart from that, the game possesses couple of merits worth to be pointed out. Despite being designed in a simplistic manner, it offers beautiful vistas. The music accompanying the course of play is remarkable on its own, creating a decent atmosphere. Unfortunately, when it comes to contents, the puzzles are either straightforward or frustratingly hard, including some obsolete-minded solutions, such as dragging the face along the walls throughout several impressively large areas, just to find that little secret. To summarise, if you seek loosePortal-meets-Tomb-Raider-type atmospheric exploration available at low cost, getKairo. If you want intellectually challenging journey in the vein ofAntichamber, move on."
