,Recommended,233230,10812665,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,ethepriest,"At first I thought this was another weird artsy fartsy game, but man, was I proved wrong. It's a semi-complex first person puzzle game that boasts a stylish yet minimalistic design that keeps you intrigued. Albeit, at times, the graphics can look a bit bland or bad, I overlook the aforementioned flaws because of how interesting the game is. A few of the puzzles actually require a bit of thinking as opposed to just flat out putting pieces wherever you feel they go. Luckily, there is a hint option in the pause screen. I had been eyeing this game for a while and saw it go on sale a couple of days ago. I highly recommend this game if you are intrigued by visual puzzles."
