,Recommended,233230,20017245,"Posted: 27 December, 2015",all,-=TheDoctor=-,"A strange, short, intriguing little game. I'd say I enjoyed it for the most part.Gameplay: The puzzles are usually pretty decent and not too difficult to figure out. However, there are times when it takes too much trial and error and guesswork rather than intuition and observation. I played through this with a walkthrough open in another tab because I found myself getting frustrated with certain puzzles. Most of them, however, are pretty straightforward. Besides the puzzles, this game is a walking simulator with some interesting environments.Graphics: Nothing special. It runs well and is ocassionally pretty to look at, but is mostly pretty bland.Level Design: The environments are neat but I felt like it could've been designed better and been more polished. I've played loads of other trippy indie games such as this, and this one really felt like it was lacking in level design creativity. Most of the environments are pretty blocky and boring, and every room is a different shade of one color.Story: As is common with these strange indie games, the story isn't too important. From what I gathered, you're exploring old ruins and contraptions and you're reactivating them, bringing life back to these environments. That's the jist, it's nothing special.Overall, I enjoyed the experience, and the length was just about right. If it had gone on longer I feel like I would've gotten sick of it. There's lots of secrets to keep you busy if you're an achievment hunter, but the gameplay wasn't interesting enough for me to find all of the secrets. Get it on a sale if you're into these kinds of games. 6/10"
,Recommended,233230,20687171,"Posted: 22 January, 2016",all,Walpy,"Good puzzles. Some was easy, some requied time to think, some (really hard) I left unsolved (yeah, I gave up easilly)To proseed the main game scenario, you have solve middle complexity puzzles, you don't have to solve them all (that's a plus for the game).Good soundtrack. Well, sometimes I felt a lack of it. In such cases, I usually turn on something on my own (ambient would be appropriate here), but not this time. The Silence. Silence of dead world. Only ruins of forgotten ancient civilization. Only you and your thoughts. Sometimes you can here someone voice. Man repeating ""zero"" or counting in russian ""five, six, seven"". But these voices also dead. Just echo of this long dead world.Good atmosphere. All that place remind me of piramids. Acient civilization, secret knowledges way beyond ours. But devistated world. Looks like one of scenario of human race.If my memmory correct, kairo translates from Japanese as ""going back home"" or smth like that. But you here all alone. In world, that was prosperous, rich, just like ours, but then... wars... doesn't seems like that... they learn lesson of war, I think... devastation... may be it happend with human race.SummaryPuzzles + atmosphere + depression + creepy. Not masterpice, but totaly worth one long night on your own. And tottaly worth it's money.P.S. Sorry, I know my review a bit... a lot fragmented. Just sometimes hard to put words logically, esspecially on alien to you language"
,Recommended,233230,20616132,"Posted: 18 January, 2016",all,spikywarkitten,"I liked it.The game has a nice surreal ambiance and sorta eerie music. You walk through majestic and mysterious places solving puzzles, some simple, some that might need a google search. Only once did I actually need a google search to help me solve a puzzle (turns out i was right about how to solve it, was just applying it incorrectly). Solving every secret and puzzle, especially those not required to beat the game, will definitely take an internet search to finish.Gameplay only requires moving and the rare jump and nothing else. There are no other requirements, all puzzles are solved with simply walking, and buttons/interactive objects are used simply by walking up to/on them. The simplicity of both gameplay and the story telling is not for everyone, but I personally loved the game.I would recommend this game for people who enjoying exploring and doing unrequired things in games and also enjoy puzzles and deep thinking. If you prefer very linear and directed gameplay or don't enjoy going outside of the main story to explore, you probably will dislike the game."
