,Recommended,233230,30988185,Posted: 6 April,all,nassi,"Even if the bland and desolate landscapes compliment the theme of the game, at some points it was taken too far and made some parts quite a chore. The storyline puzzles were of good difficulty, but for the hidden puzzles I had to consult a guide. Perhaps they would've been doable with careful note taking. The runes were of OK difficulty, although I only realized they existed at the end of the first area.Ran smoothly on my 2955U (1.4 GHz dualcore) 2GB RAM machine using the PS3 SIXAXIS controller via xboxdrv. Controls were decent enough, although the character had quite a bit of momentum. In my opinion the run could've been used by default while holding a button had made the character walk.TL;DR: A decent game if you like some FPS adventuring and puzzle solving. Bought at a discount, but even the asking price isn't bad for what the game offers."
